    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "<!--\r\n**PLEASE READ THIS FIRST:**\r\n- DO NOT use the bug and feature tracker for general questions and support requests.\r\n  Use the `cython-users` mailing list instead.\r\n  It has a wider audience, so you get more and better answers.\r\n- Did you search for similar issues already?\r\n  Please do, it helps to save us precious time that we otherwise could not invest into development.\r\n- Did you try the latest master branch or pre-release?\r\n  It might already have what you want to report.\r\n  Also see the [Changelog](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/CHANGES.rst) regarding recent changes.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nWe found out a possible segfault in the exception handling code of [lxml](https://pypi.org/project/lxml/) 4.7.1 generated with Cython (running Python 3.7).\r\n\r\nThe problematic code generated with Cython:\r\n```C\r\n__pyx_t_6 = __Pyx_PyErr_ExceptionMatches(__pyx_builtin_ImportError);\r\nif (__pyx_t_6) {\r\n  __Pyx_AddTraceback(\"lxml.etree\", __pyx_clineno, __pyx_lineno,\r\n__pyx_filename);\r\n  if (__Pyx_GetException(&__pyx_t_15, &__pyx_t_14, &__pyx_t_1) < 0) ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe issue is that between the condition check and the `__Pyx_GetException()` call, the exception can in some cases be reset in `__Pyx_AddTraceback()` function.\r\n\r\nThe complete call trace is here (Python 3.7):\r\n\r\n_lxml_ - etree.c\r\n-> `__Pyx_AddTraceback()` -> `__Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback()`\r\n_CPython_ - codeobject.c\r\n-> [`PyCode_NewEmpty()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Objects/codeobject.c#L245)\r\n_CPython_ - unicodeobject.c\r\n-> [`PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefault()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Objects/unicodeobject.c#L3666) -> [`PyUnicode_DecodeFSDefaultAndSize()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Objects/unicodeobject.c#L3686) -> [`PyUnicode_Decode()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Objects/unicodeobject.c#L3237)\r\n_CPython_ - codecs.c\r\n-> [`_PyCodec_DecodeText()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Python/codecs.c#L618) -> [`_PyCodec_DecodeInternal()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Python/codecs.c#L471)\r\n_CPython_ - call.c\r\n-> [`PyEval_CallObject()`](https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/387f93c156288c170ff0016a75af06e109d48ee1/Objects/call.c#L802) - this should not be called with active exception (as the commend there says).\r\n\r\nThe execution takes a slightly different path in our case when using Python 3.9, but the 'exception clearing functions' can still be called in some circumstances.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nCode to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n\r\nWe hit this only when using specific locale setting `LANG=\"en_US.ISO8859-15\"` (so that additional decoding is necessary). The interpreter doesn't always segfault, but running with gdb\r\n```shell\r\n> LC_ALL=\"\" LANG=\"en_US.ISO8859-15\"  gdb --args /usr/bin/python3.7 -Esc 'from lxml import etree'\r\n```\r\n```gdb\r\nb __Pyx_AddTraceback\r\ny\r\nr\r\nb PyEval_CallObjectWithKeywords\r\nb __Pyx__GetException\r\nc\r\n```\r\nclearly shows that in between `__Pyx_AddTraceback()` and `__Pyx__GetException()` breakpoints, `PyEval_CallObjectWithKeywords()` is hit.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nNo segfault - I believe that the exception should be saved and restored after the problematic call.\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Oracle Solaris 11.4 (but I do believe this can be hit by other OSes as well)\r\n - Python version 3.7 (but can be hit in 3.9 as well)\r\n - The same code is generated with Cython 29.21 (used to build lxml 4.7.1, I believe), Cython 29.28 and 3.0.0a10.\r\n\r\n**Possible fix**\r\nAfter using the following patch on lxml, the segfault is gone:\r\n```C\r\n--- lxml-4.7.1/src/lxml/etree.c\r\n+++ lxml-4.7.1/src/lxml/etree.c\r\n@@ -267792,8 +267792,14 @@ static void __Pyx_AddTraceback(const cha\r\n     }\r\n     py_code = __pyx_find_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line);\r\n     if (!py_code) {\r\n+        /* __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback can in some cases subsequently\r\n+           call functions that cannot be called with set exceptions */\r\n+        PyObject *etype, *eval, *etb;\r\n+        PyErr_Fetch(&etype, &eval, &etb);\r\n         py_code = __Pyx_CreateCodeObjectForTraceback(\r\n             funcname, c_line, py_line, filename);\r\n+        PyErr_Restore(etype, eval, etb);\r\n+\r\n         if (!py_code) goto bad;\r\n         __pyx_insert_code_object(c_line ? -c_line : py_line, py_code);\r\n     }\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2022-04-07T20:54:03Z",
