            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for investigating this. Yes, this is an issue. And the fix you provide also seems ok. There is no performance issue here since we should normally have a cached code object already.\r\n\r\nHowever, if the code object creation fails, then we shouldn't reset the exception here but clear the fetched exception references and propagate the new exception (`goto bad`). This will mostly likely only happen with memory allocation issues.",
